==Hebrew==
===Proper noun===
'''יְהֹוָה''' (Adonai)

#[[YHVH]], the [[Tetragrammaton]], the [[ineffable]] personal name of [[God]]. It is written in Hebrew with the vowels for [[Adonai]] ([[אֲדֹנָי]]) and pronounced ‘Adonai,’ because the true pronunciation of יהוה is too holy for man’s use. Outside of prayer, the Tetragrammaton is usually pronounced HaShem (The Name) or Ado-Shem (Lord’s Name) because [[Adonai]] itself is too holy for ordinary use.

